  "texts": [
    "The singular values {σ i (Φ t)} r A i=1 of Φ t give the arc-cosine of the principal angles between the two subspaces spanned by bases X t and U, respectively.",
    "In other words, {σ i (Φ t)} r A i=1 capture the alignment of the subspaces, yielding",
    "as a suitable metric to measure total alignment; see more in Appendix C.1.",
    "Analogous statements apply to {σ i (Ψ t)} r A i=1.",
    "This alignment perspective further complements the discussion of direction-magnitude decomposition in the context of equation (2)."
  ],
